                        <outline text="MC2 Linear Program Formulation #slide " _note="https://dynalist.io/d/gcskC8EanDTKsGE-U8yP7HPC#z=VHYWWW5R0cGXAErTWOSzPpr2">
                            <outline text="MC2 LP:">
<outline text="Consider">
    <outline text="&quot;$$\max C^\top y+d$$&quot; subject to &quot;$$Ay\le B$$&quot; and $$y\ge 0$$ ($$d&gt;0$$). "/>
</outline>
<outline text="This means">
    <outline text="$$\exist\, x,y^0\ge 0:\; z=x(C^\top y + d)$$ maximal s.t. $$Ay \le By^o,\; y\ge 0$$."/>
</outline>
<outline text="Here:">
    <outline text="Multiple objectives: $$C$$"/>
    <outline text="Multiple constraints: $$B$$"/>
</outline>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Necessary Conditions: Augmented Form #slide ">
                            <outline text="We view the linear system of inequalities used in the MC2 LP as a system of linear matrix equations."/>
                            <outline text="This can be written using non-basic and basic variables as">
<outline text="$$Ay+\hat{y}=By^o$$"/>
<outline text="$$x^o(C^\top y+d)=v$$"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="where $$y\ge 0,\hat{y}\ge 0,y^o\ge 0$$."/>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Constructing A Basic Solution #slide ">
                            <outline text="We can construct a basic solution that may be infeasible, or not even real, given as follows:">
<outline text="Let $$\lambda\neq 0$$ be an eigenvalue of $$D$$ with corresponding eigenvectors $$\hat{x}^\top, \hat{y}$$ and define $$\hat{v}=1/\lambda$$. "/>
<outline text="Subject to the substitution $$A\leftarrow A+aD$$ for a suitable positive real number $$a$$ we can assume $$\Re(\hat{v})&gt;0$$. "/>
<outline text="Then $$(\hat{v},\hat{x}^\top, \hat{y})$$ is a generalised eigensystem of $$I-\lambda{D}$$. "/>
<outline text="Set $$x^o=\hat{x}B$$, $$y=0$$, $$v=x^od$$ and $$y^o=C^\top \hat{y}$$."/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Sufficient Conditions for Feasible Basic Solution #slide "/>
                        <outline text="Tableau Notation #slide ">
                            <outline text="The classical compact tableau notation is expanded as follows:">
<outline text="$$\begin{array}{|c|c|c|} \hline A &amp; I &amp; B\\ \hline C^\top &amp; 0 &amp; V\\ \hline \end{array}$$"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="The dual tableau is:">
<outline text="$$\begin{array}{|c|c|} \hline A  &amp; B\\ \hline I  &amp; 0 \\ \hline C^\top  &amp; V\\ \hline \end{array}$$"/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
