                        <outline text="On the equivalence of rank-$$k$$ VN Models and MC2 optimisation. #h ">
                            <outline text="STATUS" colorLabel="1"/>
                            <outline text="Background">
<outline text="https://dynalist.io/d/gcskC8EanDTKsGE-U8yP7HPC#z=NtPJeQOOEbhDA2xgUzbz8UVK"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="LP Equivalence Theorem #slide ">
<outline text="Consider the model VNM($$D,A$$) where $$D=BC^\top \geqq 0$$."/>
<outline text="We refer to this as a rank-1 VN model."/>
<outline text="It is known in the literature \cite{Bidard2000-jr}, that such a model is equivalent to a linear program."/>
<outline text="Theorem: the rank-one model VNM($$uv^\top,A$$) with maximal growth factor $$\lambda&gt;0$$ is equivalent to the linear program LP($$v^\top, A, u$$) with optimal value $$\lambda^{-1}$$. #theorem "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="Proof #slide ">
<outline text="$$\Longrightarrow$$&quot; ">
    <outline text="Let $$A=UV^\top$$ with $$U, V\in\R^{n\times k}$$ having full rank ($$k\le n$$)."/>
    <outline text="We start with $$\lambda$$ maximal such that $$\exists x,y\in \R^{n}: x^\top(A-\lambda UV^\top)\geqq 0$$."/>
    <outline text="Define $$\tilde{X} := \lambda^{-1} {(X^\top U)}^{-1}X^\top$$."/>
    <outline text="Then $$\tilde{X}u=\frac{X^\top U}{\lambda X^\top U}=\lambda^{-1}$$ is minimal, such that $$\tilde{X}^\top(A-\lambda UV^\top)=\tilde{X}^\top A-V^\top \geqq 0$$."/>
    <outline text="This means that the multi-linear multi-criteria program MLC($$U, A, V^\top$$) is solved by $$\tilde{X}^\top$$ with value $$\lambda^{-1}$$."/>
</outline>
<outline text="&quot;$$\Longleftarrow$$&quot; ">
    <outline text="Assume $${X}^\top$$ is a solution of the multi-linear multi-criteria program MLC($$U, A, V^\top$$) with value $$\mu^{}$$."/>
    <outline text="This means $$\mu := X^\top u$$ is minimal such that $$X^\top A-V^\top\geqq 0$$."/>
    <outline text="One has $$V^\top=(X^\top U)^{-1}X^\top UV^\top = \mu^{-1}X^\top UV^\top \geqq 0$$. "/>
    <outline text="Hence $$X^\top(A-\mu^{-1} UV^\top)\geqq 0$$ and $$\lambda:=\mu^{-1}$$ is a maximal growth factor for VNM($$UV^\top,A$$)."/>
</outline>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
