                        <outline text="Random Oracle Model #slide ">
                            <outline text="A random oracle $$\mathcal O$$ is a deterministic function, mapping input into an output domain, following a uniformly random distribution. "/>
                            <outline text="This can be used as a theoretical model for a range of cryptographic primitives:">
<outline text="Provably secure encryption algorithms [@Bellare1993]"/>
<outline text="True random number generators and secure hash functions [@Coron2000]"/>
<outline text="Define security for steganography [@Katzenbeisser], [@Hopper2002], [@Fischlin2016]"/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
