                        <outline text="INBOX  #wfe-ignore-outline ">
                            <outline text="Criminal Revenue Criminal revenue is  the  monetary equivalent of the  gross receipts from  a  crime.We do not include any lawful business expenses of the criminal.1 For example, an illicit online pharmacy may purchase hosting services from a legitimate provider and pay the market price. This reduces the c riminals profits, but contributes to the gross product of the economy in which the provider is located. 1 The UK Proceeds of Crime Act does not allow an offenders costs to be deducted from the amounthe is deemed to owe the state"/>
                            <outline text="[http://www.stuart-hall.com/2013/03/05/cba-vs-roi-cost-benefit-analysis-vs-return-on-investment/#sthash.CKL3R1cC.dpbs](http://www.stuart-hall.com/2013/03/05/cba-vs-roi-cost-benefit-analysis-vs-return-on-investment/#sthash.CKL3R1cC.dpbs)"/>
                            <outline text="[https://blog.netwrix.com/2020/07/24/annual-loss-expectancy-and-quantitative-risk-analysis/](https://blog.netwrix.com/2020/07/24/annual-loss-expectancy-and-quantitative-risk-analysis/)"/>
                        </outline>
