            <outline text="We denote the __spectrum__ of a regular matrix pencil, which may comprise of both finite eigenvalues and the eigenvalue at infinity, as $$\sigma(A-\lambda B)=\sigma^\circ(A-\lambda B)\cup\sigma^\infty(A-\lambda B)$$."/>
