<outline text="First Minor and Co-factor">
    <outline text="The (__i__, __j__) or __first minor__ $$M_{i,j}$$ of the entry in the __i__th row and __j__th column is the determinant of the submatrix formed by deleting the __i__th row and __j__th column."/>
    <outline text="The (__i__, __j__) __cofactor__ $$C_{i,j}$$ is obtained by the minor as follows: $$ C_{i,j}=(-1)^{i+j}M_{i,j}$$. "/>
</outline>
<outline text="Principal Minor ">
    <outline text="A principal minor is simply the determinant of a submatrix obtained from A when the same set of rows and columns are deleted."/>
</outline>
