                            <outline text="The Method #h ">
<outline text="Initialisation #slide #simplex:init ">
    <outline text="We start with a basic solution: ">
        <outline text="$$\hat{v}=\frac{1}{c^\top b}$$, $$\hat{x}^\top=c^\top$$, $$\hat{y}=b$$."/>
    </outline>
    <outline text="We can see that $$(\hat{v},\hat{x}^\top, \hat{y})$$ is a generalised eigensystem of $$I-\lambda {bc^\top}$$."/>
    <outline text="This will only give feasible solutions, if $$b \geqq 0$$ or $$c \geqq 0$$."/>
</outline>
<outline text="Reduction Step #slide "/>
<outline text="Termination #slide #simplex:exit ">
    <outline text="Criterium: $$b \geq 0$$ and $$c^\top \geq 0$$."/>
    <outline text="Maximising $$z_k= {d}^\top_{k}+{c}^\top_{k} x_k$$ and $${c}^\top_{k} \leqq 0$$ is solved by $$x_k=0$$. "/>
    <outline text="The iterations terminate with $$x=x_{{k}}=0$$ and $$\hat{x}=\hat{x}_{{k}}$$ if $$\tilde{c}^\top\leqq 0$$, "/>
    <outline text="Note that since $${v}=\frac{1}{c^\top A^{-1}b}&gt;0$$,"/>
    <outline text=""/>
    <outline text=" we can assume $${v}&gt;0$$, $$A&gt;0$$ and hence $$A^{-1}&gt;0$$."/>
    <outline text=" $${x}^\top=c^\top A^{-1}$$, $${y}=A^{-1}b$$, $$x$$ and $$y$$ are feasible."/>
    <outline text="Furthermore $$\hat{x} = 0$$ and $$\hat{y} = 0$$."/>
    <outline text="or with $$\hat{x}_{{k}}=0$$ if $$A^{-1}b\geqq 0$$. #lemma "/>
</outline>
