                    <outline text="Multi-Criteria (MC2) Linear Programming #h">
                        <outline text="Definition #slide ">
                            <outline text="A standard form of the LP is to choose $$x_1,\ldots,x_n$$, to maximize">
<outline text="$$ c_1x_1 + \cdots + c_nx_n$$, "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="subject to the constraints">
<outline text="$$a_{11}x_1 + \cdots + a_{1n}x_n \le b_1$$"/>
<outline text="  $$\vdots$$"/>
<outline text="$$a_{m1}x_1 + \cdots + a_{mn}x_n \le b_m$$"/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="and">
<outline text="$$x_j \ge 0$$  for $$ j = 1,\ldots,n$$."/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="In compact notation this is:">
<outline text="MAX $$c^T x$$  ST $$Ax\le b$$ and $$x\ge 0$$. "/>
                            </outline>
                        </outline>
                        <outline text="Dual Linear Optimisation Problem -- Definition #slide ">
                            <outline text="Find $$x,y$$: #deconstruct:equilibrium">
<outline text="$$\min c^\top y$$  subject to $$Ay\ge b$$ and $$y\ge 0$$. "/>
<outline text="$$\max   x^\top b$$  subject to $$x^\top A\le c^\top$$ and $$x\ge 0$$. "/>
                            </outline>
                            <outline text="Strong Duality Theorem:">
<outline text="Denote $$v^{+} := \min c^\top y,v^{-}:=\max x^\top b$$."/>
<outline text="The following theorem holds:"/>
<outline text="#theorem: $$v^{-}=v^{+}$$."/>
